                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                           <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works. Occasionally God is written in alternating red and black letters (e.g., <locus target="#2v" facs="003">fol. 2v</locus>)</desc>
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                           <desc>The word Mary is rubricated in the final two works. </desc>
                        </seg>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#110v #111r" facs="111 111">folss. 110v, 111r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#119v #120r #120v" facs="120 120 121">119v, 120r, 120v</locus> (tenth Biblical Canticle)</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#148v" facs="149">Fol. 148v</locus>
                        <desc> Crude drawing of a rider on a horse</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r #13v #20r #40r #48v #72r #105r" facs="001 014 020 040 049 072 105">folss. 1r, 13v, 20r, 40r, 48v, 72r, 105r, </locus> (haräg)
                  <locus target="#7r">7r, </locus> (multiple full stops and a line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#84r" facs="084">84r</locus> (line of red and black dots)
                </decoNote>
                 </decoDesc>
                 <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <locus target="#146v #147r" facs="147 147">Fols. 146v, 147r</locus>
                           <desc>mention <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3500Demetriu">Demetrius II of Alexandria</persName> (II 1862–70) and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2209Athanasi">Athanasius</persName> (1869–1876)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                          <locus target="#147v" facs="148">Fol. 147v</locus>
                           <desc>mentions Emperor <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> (1868–1913)
                      </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                          <locus target="#148v" facs="149">Fol. 148v</locus>
                           <desc>mentions the name of a scribe, <q>“A good pentrial; the scribe is Ḫabtä Maryam.”</q></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                      Through Psalm 106, the numbers ten <foreign xml:lang="gez">(፲)</foreign> and twelve <foreign xml:lang="gez">(፲፪)</foreign> are in the margins throughout, indicating sections of ten or twelve lines in the text, probably for use with antiphonal readings for morning prayers                     </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                          <locus target="#54r" facs="054">Fol. 54r</locus>
                           <desc>the mid-point of the Psalter is marked with the words <q>“Half of David.”</q></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                    Identified in the insurance hand list as Psalter 3
                    </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                          <locus target="#13 #28 #48 #59 #67 #84 #99 #111" facs="013 028 048 059 067 084 099 111">Fols. 13, 28, 48, 59, 67, 84, 99, 111</locus>
                           <desc>Red fabric is sewn into the fore edge as navigation system</desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                       <locus target="#7 #20 #35 #72 #96 #105" facs="007 020 035 072 096 105">Fols. 7, 20, 35, 72, 96, 105</locus>
                       <desc>Yellow fabric sewn into the fore edge as navigation system</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                          <locus target="#2v #5v #6r #6v #14r">Fols. 2v, 5v, 6r, 6v, 14r</locus>
                           <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                          <locus target="#16v #32r #44v #49r #51r" facs="017 032 045 049 051">Fols. 16v, 32r, 44v, 49r, 51r</locus>
                        <desc>etc., lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                          <locus target="#75r" facs="075">f. 75r line 13</locus>
                          <locus target="#85r" facs="085">f. 85r line 12</locus>
                          <locus target="#87r" facs="087">f. 87r line 16</locus>
                          <locus target="#89v" facs="090">f. 89v line 18</locus>
                          <locus target="#101r" facs="101">f. 101r line 16</locus>
                          <desc>lines are text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                          </item>
                        <item xml:id="e10">
                          <locus target="#8v #14v #22v #23r #27v" facs="009 015 023 023 028">Fols. 8v, 14v, 22v, 23r, 27v</locus>
                          <desc>etc., text has been removed</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
